				<h3>A major in Art consits of the following:</h3>
				<h4>31 hours in the following art core:</h4>
				 
				<ul>
					<li>ART 113 - Art Fundamentals: Theory and Practice</li>
					<li>ART 122 - Art History I: Ancient, Medieval, and Non-European Art</li>
					<li>ART 124 - Art History II: Renaissance to the Present</li>
					<li>ART 212 - Drawing I</li>
					<li>ART 232 - Design I: 2D</li>
					<li>ART 251 - Painting I</li>
					<li>ART 261 - Introduction to Photography</li>
					<li>ART 303 - Design II: 3D</li>
					<li>ART 385 - Printmaking</li>
					<li>ART 430 - Senior Exhibit/Portfolio</li>
					<li>ART 460 - Issues in Contemporary Art</li>
				</ul>
	
				<h4>9 hours in emphasis area:</h4>
				<h5>Ceramics</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>ART 375 - Ceramics I</li>
					<li>ART 376 - Ceramics II</li>
					<li>ART 476 - Ceramics III</li>
				</ul>
	
				<h5>Drawing</h5> 
				<ul>
					<li>ART 312 - Drawing II</li>
					<li>ART 342 - Life Drawing</li>
					<li>ART 442 - Advanced Drawing</li>
				</ul>
				
				<h5>Fiber Arts</h5> 
				<ul>
					<li>ART 381 - Fiber Arts I: General</li>
					<li>ART 382 - Fiber Arts II</li>
					<li>ART 483 - Fiber Arts III</li>
				</ul>
				
				<h5>Graphics</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>ART 271 - Graphics I: Visual Design</li>
					<li>ART 321 - Graphics II: Typography</li>
					<li>ART 323 - Graphics III: Computer-Assisted Design</li>
				</ul>
				
				<h5>Painting</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>ART 351 - Oil/Acrylic Painting II</li>
					<li>ART 451 - Oil/Acrylic Painting III</li>
					<li>ART 452 - Advanced Painting</li>
				</ul>
				
				<h5>Photography</h5>
				<ul>
					<li>ART 363 - Advanced Photography</li>
					<li>ART 461 - Fine Art Photography I</li>
					<li>ART 462 - Fine Art Photography II</li>
				</ul>
				
				<h5>9 hours in studio electives</h5>
